snippet.textDisplay:
Hello Dax, my name is David and I am a strong believer in Jesus Christ. I listened to your song, and I loved it. You have a lot of questions, you say there are no answers. Is that true? If you read Gods word you will see he has an answer for everything in your song, one of the many things that stood out to me in this song, was the part at the end, when you said “what if the place where we grew up forgot to teach it?” Well God says in his word that he puts the thoughts of God in every mans knowledge. This means everyone will wonder about a God or higher being. Yes. Some people don’t get to learn about it correctly and know the 100% truth. But they will wonder and God WILL send someone to teach it to them. And when you said “what if we never got to get the chance to seek it?” Matthew 6:33 says “But seek first the kingdom of God and his righteousness, and all of these things will be added to you.” And also in Deuteronomy 4:29 it says “But from there you will seek the Lord your God and you will find him, if you search after him with all your heart and with all your soul.” God gives us a choice. If God gave you a choice then don’t you think he would give you the other side of the choice. Because without God we are nothing but sin. With God he gives us life and eternal love.

Also in this song you say life is all about love. But God tells us to have righteous anger. Righteous anger is the only kind of anger we are supposed to have. Righteous anger is anger against sateen and sin.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hi, I really like this song and have been listening to your tracks for a while now.
On this subject I’ve listened to many songs and every time a good one comes by (like this one) it’s really inspiring! This track is very well-done bro!

On the subject; writing is a personal therapy for me, I think you can understand what I mean ;), but the reason I share this is that maybe you understand what I really MEAN, and what the MEANING of it is…
I wrote this once after listening to Hopsin's Number 8,

Dear God, could you talk to me?
I'm writing now,
This is how,
I present my thoughts to thee.
Why is the truth to far to see?
Why does everything look like a farce to me?
Growing up with questions and committing to different masteries,
To blowing up perceptions and sitting through these blasphemies.
Instead of having the experience we think How it ought to be.
Like we start off with a lobotomy,
From the moment we are born,
Thrown into this world and twirl while our minds are torn,
Into a COMMODITY!


As thoughts speed up, I turn the heat up,
Turn up a beat, take a seat, and put my feet up,
Got all I need, my mind freed, I roll my weed up.


I need you to teach me.
So many have tried,
With good intentions and lies,
But none seem to reach me.
Sheep repeating other sheep,
Thinking with low esteem.
Asleep deep under the sheets,
Sinking into the dream.


Will we ever get to wake up and shake up this place?
Where clowns wear the crown.
Or will we never brake and stop to break up this pace?
That actually slows us down…
I'm trying to believe, really, I have more then tried
But what do we achieve, if we glorify,
Everything that to me only horrifies?
Listen to authority,


Don't even know a real leader.
To make you feel,
you are holding on to something real.
But deep down you are just a bottom feeder.
Cannot even feel the weight on your shoulders no more.
Life is so great; it just doesn't show like before.
You're just full of hate,
That happens when your heart gets sore.
Right... Like I have never had anything to thrive towards?
Like these words are just the curse of a mind that's bored...




For Dax:


Allow me to write,
These bright words so they may draw light,
Wherever a spark is needed to escape the dark,
Or to win your fight,
Embark on this journey,
And make your mark in this Life, As is your right.


I hope you bring to nutrition well this conditioning,
And bring to Fruition, all that you have been envisioning.

Pat Zilla #BeBlessed
